</br>15 Finally the water became exhausted in the skin bottle and she threw the child under one of the bushes.
</br>16 Then she went on and sat down by herself, about the distance of a bowshot away, because she said: “Let me not see it when the child dies.” So she sat down at a distance and began to raise her voice and weep.
