</br>9 God now appeared to Jacob once again during his coming from Pad´dan-a´ram and blessed him.
</br>10 And God went on to say to him: “Your name is Jacob. No longer is your name to be called Jacob, but Israel will your name become.” And he began to call his name Israel.
</br>11 And God said further to him: “I am God Almighty. Be fruitful and become many. Nations and a congregation of nations will proceed out of you, and kings will come out of your loins.
</br>12 As for the land that I have given to Abraham and to Isaac, to you I shall give it, and to your seed after you I shall give the land.”
</br>13 After that God went up from above him at the place where he had spoken with him.
<p></p>
